# No links to draft insight articles

Docusaurus **excludes** pages with `draft: true` from production builds. Any link from a published page to a draft slug fails `onBrokenLinks` and breaks the build.

## Rule

When you **create** an insight article with `draft: true`, or **set** `draft: true` on an existing one:

1. **Do not add** links to that article from any other doc page (insights, playbooks, blueprints, frameworks, etc.).
2. **Remove or replace** existing inbound links before leaving the article as draft.

Draft articles may still link **out** to published pages. The ban is on **inbound** links only.

## How to identify draft targets

Check frontmatter in `docs/insights/**/*.mdx`:

```yaml
slug: before-training-an-llm
draft: true
```

Link paths use the slug: `/insights/before-training-an-llm`.

Before adding `[text](/insights/<slug>)`, confirm the target file does **not** have `draft: true`.

## When publishing

Remove `draft: true` (or set `draft: false`) **first**, then add inbound links from other pages.

## Examples

```markdown
# BAD — published page links to a draft insight
Deep dive: [The Blueprint Before Training](/insights/before-training-an-llm)

# GOOD — wait until draft is removed, or use plain text with no link
Deep dive: The Blueprint Before Training (coming soon)

# GOOD — after draft: true is removed from the target
Deep dive: [The Blueprint Before Training](/insights/before-training-an-llm)
```

## Before finishing

1. If you added or kept `draft: true`, grep the repo for `/insights/<slug>` and remove inbound links.
2. If you linked to an insight from another doc, verify the target is not draft.
3. Do not add `:::info[Builds on]` or body cross-links from published pages to draft slugs.
